\title{Fine-Gray Competing Risks Learner}
\description{
Fine-Gray subdistribution hazards model for competing risks using
\code{\link[cmprsk:crr]{cmprsk::crr()}}.
}
\details{
The fitted model is an S3 object of class \code{"fine_gray"} that stores a
cause-specific list of \code{crr} class models.

At prediction time, each cause-specific model is evaluated with
\code{\link[cmprsk:predict.crr]{cmprsk::predict.crr()}} and the resulting CIF matrices are aligned to a common
time grid across causes using constant CIF interpolation.
The time grid is the \strong{unique event times (across all causes)} observed in the training set.

Time-interaction terms (via \code{cov2}) are not implemented.
}
